plugins/adminmanager/commands.html.title: Commands | Alpalis Docs
plugins/adminmanager/commands.html.keywords: Commands Command(Aliases) Subcommand(Aliases) Description AdminMode Required Command Actor /adminmode <get/switch> Command to manage the admin mode. - get [player] (<player>)¹ Command to get state of your or player's admin mode. - switch [player] (<player>) Command to turn on and off the admin mode. /fly <get/switch> Command to manage the fly modes. - get [player] (<player>) Command to get state of your or player's fly modes. - switch [player] (<player>) Command to turn on and off the fly mode. [ ✓ ] /god <get/switch> Command to manage the god modes. [ — ] - get [player] (<player>) Command to turn on and off the god modes. [ ✓ ] - switch [player] (<player>) Command to get state of your or player's god modes. [ ✓ ] /vanish <get/switch> Command to manage the vanish. [ — ] - get [player] (<player>) Command to get state of your or player's vanish. [ ✓ ] - switch [player] (<player>) Command to turn on and off the vanish. [ ✓ ] /food [player] (<player>) Command to update food for yourself and other players. [ ✓ ] /heal [player] (<player>) Command to heal yourself and other players. [ ✓ ] /virus [player] (<player>) Command to set virus for yourself and other players. [ ✓ ] /water [player] (<player>) Command to set water for yourself and other players. [ ✓ ] /compass [North/South/East/West] Command that shows direction you are facing or turn to face a specific direction [ ✓ ] /position [player] (<player>) Command that shows your or somebody's position. [ ✓ ] /rotation [player] (<player>) Command that shows your or somebody's rotation. [ ✓ ] /tps Command that shows TPS. [ ✓ ] /annoucement <message> Command to post annoucements. [ ✓ ] /chat <clear/enable/disable> Command to manage chat. [ X ] - clear Command to clear chat. [ ✓ ] - disable Command to disable chat. [ ✓ ] - enable Command to enable chat. [ ✓ ] /ascend(up) [distance] Command that teleports you up. [ ✓ ] /descend(down) [distance] Command that teleports you down. [ ✓ ] /jump(jmp) Jump to where you're looking. [ ✓ ] /gravity <multipler> [player] (<multipler> <player>) Command to set gravity. [ ✓ ] /jumpheight <multipler> [player] (<multipler> <player>) Command to set jump height. [ ✓ ] /speed <multipler> [player] (<multipler> <player>) Command to set speed. [ ✓ ] /teleport(tp) [player] <player/place/marker> (<player> <player/place>) Command to teleport player to another player or place. [ ✓ ] /experience(exp) <get/add/set/take> Command to manage your or somebody's experience. [ X ] - add <amount> [player] (<amount> <player>) Command to add your or somebody's experience. [ ✓ ] - set <amount> [player] (<amount> <player>) Command to set your or somebody's experience. [ ✓ ] - take <amount> [player] (<amount> <player>) Command to take your or somebody's experience. [ ✓ ] - get [player] (<player>) Command to get your or somebody's experience. [ — ] /maxskills [player] (<player>) Command to max your or somebody's skills. [ ✓ ] /reputation(rep) <get/add/set/take> Command to manage your or somebody's reputation. [ X ] - add <amount> [player] (<amount> <player>) Command to add your or somebody's reputation. [ ✓ ] - set <amount> [player] (<amount> <player>) Command to set your or somebody's reputation. [ ✓ ] - take <amount> [player] (<amount> <player>) Command to take your or somebody's reputation. [ ✓ ] - get [player] (<player>) Command to get your or somebody's reputation. [ — ] /clear <items/vehicles/inventory> (<inventory>) Command to clear items, vehicles or inventories. [ X ] - inventory [player] (<player>) Command to clear inventories. [ ✓ ] - items <distance> Command to clear items laying on the ground. [ ✓ ] - vehicles <distance> [clearLocked] Command to clear vehicles. [ ✓ ] /destroy Command to destroy object you're looking at. [ ✓ ] /exit Command to fast exit the server. [ ✓ ] /item(i) <item> [amount] [player] (<item> <amount> <player>) Command to give items. [ ✓ ] /join <ip/domain> <port> [password] Command to join another server. [ ✓ ] /kill [player] (<player>) Command to kill yourself or another player. [ ✓ ] /more [amount] Command to duplicate the item you are holding. [ ✓ ] /open Command to force open door, storage and vehicles. [ ✓ ] /owner Command to check owner of object you're looking at. [ ✓ ] /refuel Command to refuel the object you're looking at or current vehicle. [ ✓ ] /repair Command to repair the object you're looking at or current vehicle. [ ✓ ] /requesturl <url> [player] [message] (<url> <player> [message]) Command to request player to open URL. [ ✓ ] /respawn <zombie/animals/vehicles> Command to respawn entities. [ X ] - animals(animal) Command to respawn animals. [ ✓ ] - zombies(zombie) Command to respawn zombies. [ ✓ ] - vehicles(vehicle) Command to respawn vehicles. [ ✓ ] /salvagespeed <multipler> [player] (<multipler> <player>) Command to set speed of salvage. [ ✓ ] /time <get/set> Command to change or get overworld time. [ X ] - get Command to get overworld time. [ ✓ ] - set <time> Command to set overworld time. [ ✓ ] /tphere <player> Command that teleports player to you. [ ✓ ] /vehicle(i) <vehicle> [player] (<vehicle> <player>) Command to spawn vehicles. [ ✓ ] /weather <set/disable> Command to change overworld weather. [ X ] - set <sunny/storm/blizzard> Command to set overworld weather. [ ✓ ] - disable Command to disable overworld weather. [ ✓ ] ¹ - syntax for the command called in the console
